To prevent the ends from fraying, you may finish the straps in one of two ways. Tack down the ends of the straps. Fold over the end of one strap and secure it in place with a pin. Thread a needle and proceed to tack down the end of one strap. Repeat this process on the other strap. This application will leave your halter top looking polished. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/12/Make-a-Halter-Top-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Halter-Top-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/12/Make-a-Halter-Top-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Halter-Top-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
