Tie knots at the ends of the straps. To prevent the ends from fraying, tie one to two knots at the end of each strap. Secure the knot in place with a few stitches. This application is simpler. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b5/Make-a-Halter-Top-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Halter-Top-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b5/Make-a-Halter-Top-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Halter-Top-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
